Hotel Booking Analysis – Power BI Dashboard

1) Project Overview

This project presents a **Hotel Booking Analysis Dashboard** developed using **Power BI**.
The dashboard provides a clear overview of hotel booking patterns, customer behavior, and revenue-related metrics to support business and operational decision-making.

2) The analysis helps to understand:

* Overall booking performance
* Customer booking behavior
* Room and hotel type demand
* Cancellation trends
* Revenue-related insights

3) Tools & Technologies

* Power BI Desktop – data modeling & dashboard creation
* Hotel Booking Dataset (Excel / CSV)
* GitHub – project documentation and version control


4) Dataset Overview

The dataset contains hotel booking–related information including:

* Hotel Type (City Hotel / Resort Hotel)
* Arrival Date (Year, Month, Day)
* Number of Adults, Children, Babies
* Room Type (Reserved & Assigned)
* Stay Duration (Weekdays & Weekends)
* Booking Status (Canceled / Not Canceled)
* Lead Time
* Average Daily Rate (ADR)

---

5) Key KPIs

* Total Bookings
* Total Cancellations
* Cancellation Rate (%)
* Average Daily Rate (ADR)
* Average Length of Stay



6) Dashboard Visualizations

* KPI Cards – total bookings, cancellations, ADR
* Bar Chart – bookings by hotel type
* Line Chart – monthly booking trends
* Donut / Pie Chart – cancellation vs non-cancellation
* Column Chart – room type demand
* Slicers – hotel type, arrival month, year

---

7) Key Insights

* City hotels receive higher bookings compared to resort hotels
* A significant portion of bookings are canceled, indicating demand volatility
* Peak bookings occur during specific months/seasons
* Certain room types are booked more frequently
* Longer lead time is associated with higher cancellation probability

---

8) How to Use the Dashboard

1. Open the `.pbix` file in **Power BI Desktop**
2. Refresh the dataset if required
3. Use slicers to filter by hotel type, time period, or booking status
4. Interact with visuals to explore trends and insights

---

9) Conclusion

This dashboard demonstrates practical **data analytics and visualization skills using Power BI**, focusing on real-world hospitality data.
It is suitable for **Data Analyst / Business Analyst portfolio projects**, especially in the hospitality domain.


